<div id="pf50e1" class="pf w45 h34e" data-page-no="50e1"><div class="pc pc50e1 w45 h34e"><div class="t m109 x74 h2d y2f77 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">V. LED BY THE SPIRIT (Luke 1:6; Acts 10:1, 2). </div><div class="t m988 x60 h2d y2d70 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m223 x65 h2d y2cd9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Guidance and Power of the Spirit (Luke 12:12; Acts 1:8). </div><div class="t m481 x60 h2d y297a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke&apos;s Gospel begins with a great flurry of activity in Jerusalem and </div><div class="t mf2f x74 h2d y29f3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Nazareth as the Spirit imprints His authority of divine action on events. Acts </div><div class="t med9 x74 h2d y2991 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">resounds with the rushing wind of the Spirit as it drives the ship of the faith-</div><div class="t md28 x74 h2d y2994 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ful witness ever onward. </div><div class="t m44b x60 h2d y28dd ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke did not present the Spirit as the Giver of Christian character (Gal. </div><div class="t m625 x74 h2d y2217 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5:22, 23). He left it to Paul to convey the inner struggle between flesh and </div><div class="t m467 x74 h2d y2077 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Spirit (verses 17, 18). He did, however, capture the essence of the convict-</div><div class="t m9c1 x74 h2d y4f8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ing, converting power of the Spirit (John 16:7-10), and of the Spirit who </div><div class="t m403 x74 h2d y1c83 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">guides into truth (14:26). Above all else he knew the Spirit who testifies of </div><div class="t m45b x74 h2d y20d3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus through the believer (15:26). </div><div class="t m84d x60 h2d y18d9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What purpose does God have in giving the Spirit to every believer? </div><div class="t m6ab x74 h2d y13f1 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Acts 2:32, 33; 4:31. </div><div class="t m127 x4e h2d y13bd ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t mab2 x5b h2d ya10 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prayer Teaches Obedience and Trust (Luke 22:40, 41; Acts 20:19-</div><div class="t mce x74 h2d y83a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">24). </div><div class="t m331 x4e h2d y11e0 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How does prayer help us relate to the needs and situation of others? </div><div class="t m65e x74 h2d y11c3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 22:31, 32; Acts 12:4, 5. </div><div class="t mcf6 x4e h2d y11c5 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;It is our Lord&apos;s will that we who have received access to these powers </div><div class="t m18c3 x73 h2d y13e3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">through prayer should go through this world transmitting heavenly power to </div><div class="t m176c x73 h2d y10ea ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">every corner of a world which needs it sorely. Our lives should be, according to </div><div class="t mac1 x73 h2d y1f8a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">our Lord&apos;s plans, quiet, but steadily flowing, streams of blessing, which </div><div class="t m3a7 x73 h2d y153e ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">through our prayers and intercessions should reach our whole environ-</div><div class="t m257 x73 h2d y10f3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ment.&apos; &quot;â€”O. Hallesby, </div><div class="t ma84 x84 h4a yf39 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prayer </div><div class="t m5e5 x2a h2d y13d9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(London: W. S. Cowell Ltd., 1949), p. 51. </div><div class="t m2b6 x4e h2d y1dd0 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m6f5 x5b h2d y1602 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Living According to God&apos;s Law (Luke 10:27, 28; Acts 20:18, 19). </div><div class="t m2bf x4e h2d y10fe ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke presents a clear picture of the lifestyle expected of the follower of </div><div class="t me1a x73 h2d y1f52 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus. The follower will: </div><div class="t m1c2 x4e h2d yecf ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m27c x5b h2d y1057 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Be obedient to the commandments of God (Luke 1:6; 23:56). </div><div class="t m1c2 x4e h2d y15d4 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m1080 x5b h2d y1e9b ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Accept the will of God (Luke 1:35; Acts 5:29). </div><div class="t m1c2 x4e h2d y19d7 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t mab9 x5b h2d y19d7 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Keep the Sabbath (Luke 4:16; Acts 17:2). </div><div class="t m1c2 x4e h2d y11e5 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m73b x5b h2d y1361 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Be generous and merciful (Luke 6:36-38; Acts 20:35). </div><div class="t m1c2 x4e h2d yf4c ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m14ab x5b h2d y1248 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Be consistent and forgiving (Luke 6:41, 42). </div><div class="t m1c2 x4e h2d y156a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t mf25 x63 h2d y1e27 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Love God and neighbor (Luke 10:27). </div><div class="t maae x4e h2d y105e ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How does God expect His church to relate lifestyle to witness? Acts </div><div class="t mf5 x73 h2d y123a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">9:31; 11:23, 24. </div><div class="t m261 x4e h2d y1fea ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. Hearing God&apos;s Voice (Luke 24:32; Acts 26:19). </div><div class="t m778 x4e h2d y1347 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">No one could accept Luke and then abandon the Old Testament. The Lord </div><div class="t m148 x73 h2d ybe6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">directed His disciples to the Old Testament (Luke 24:32, 44); there the </div><div class="t mef x73 h4 y1d43 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">94 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
